blog.name: fitness-journey-of-a-fat-girl
blog.title: Everyday Is A New Day
blog.description: I’m a 23 year old college student who has struggled with weight my whole life. Recently my mother was diagnosed with diabetes and I had my own “pre-diabetic” scare. I was also diagnosed with PCOS and some mental illness. I’ve been eating the recommended diabetic carb intake since 9/12/18. I have also been a vegetarian for seven years now and I’m allergic to gluten. I have a long way to go and wanted to keep a blog of my journey! Even if I’m the only one reading this I want to be able to look back on my progress. However, I hope you come along for the ride and get something out of this! :)

title: [Question] is it ok to eat flaxseed? via /r/Paleo
body:
It has a lot of magnesium and manganese (and fibre, if that’s your thing) for starters.

On the other hand it’s low in essential fatty acids and contains phytates.

summary: Brussels to scrap migrant sea patrol rescues as Italy tightens screws on migration The EU will cease maritime patrols but extend...
caption: Brussels to scrap migrant sea patrol rescues as Italy tightens screws on migration The EU will cease maritime patrols but extend air missions, two diplomats said on Tuesday, adding that a new agreement on the bloc’s Operation Sophia was cobbled together after Italy – where anti-migrant sentiment is rife – said it would no longer take in those rescued at sea.
